text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia sulcata is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Great Southern, Goldfields-Esperance and Wheatbelt regions of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 2 metres (1 to 7 ft). It blooms from June to February and produces yellow flowers.
There are three varieties:

Acacia sulcata var. planoconvexa
Acacia sulcata var. platyphylla
Acacia sulcata var. sulcata
